President Cyril Ramaphosa will be outlining his plan for the country. It comes at a time when our economy is under pressure, prices are rising, unemployment is spiralling, we are coming to terms with the devastation of years of state capture and corruption, and the devastation of the unrest of July year. eNCA speaks to political commentator, Justice Malala. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is under pressure to implement a Basic Income Grant. Many are also calling for the extension of the R350 COVID-19 relief payments. READ: WATCH | Cape Town City Hall becomes Parliament However, one commentator says these announcements may not come during the State of the Nation Address. Justice Malala expects the President to defer it to the budget speech on 23 February. Watch the video above for more details on this story.